_**User (2025-11-12 07:52Z)**_

Verify these issues exist and fix them:

Bug 1:
ErrorActionPreference is set to "Continue" instead of "Stop". This causes the script to continue executing even if critical commands like Set-Location (lines 17, 39, 60) fail. If a directory change fails, subsequent file operations and path-dependent operations will execute in the wrong directory context, causing the build/install process to fail silently or install files in incorrect locations. This is particularly critical since the script performs multiple directory changes and makes assumptions about the current working directory for relative paths like ".codex\agents\*" on line 130.

 @build-install-commit.ps1 (12-13)
